93
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:08,439
I hope he won't be born into a family like ours in the next life.

94
00:05:11,279 --> 00:05:13,999
He went to see our parents.

95
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:17,439
But I'm not happy at all.

96
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:22,879
I don't want him to see our parents.

97
00:05:23,439 --> 00:05:24,600
I know.

98
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:26,720
Ms. Wu.

99
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,719
You can miss him.

100
00:05:31,679 --> 00:05:33,279
You can feel sad.

101
00:05:34,119 --> 00:05:36,279
But you should continue your life.

102
00:05:37,119 --> 00:05:41,399
Lead a good life with the hope of your brother.

103
00:06:44,439 --> 00:06:45,239
Sun.

104
00:06:50,279 --> 00:06:51,959
A'Li, you had a nightmare.

105
00:06:52,719 --> 00:06:54,839
You repeatedly called Sun.

106
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:56,800
Who is he?

107
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,398
Nothing.

108
00:06:59,399 --> 00:07:02,239
You shouldn't shut yourself up in your room every day.

109
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:04,838
One will think too much if staying alone for a long time.

110
00:07:04,839 --> 00:07:07,800
What you dream about at night reflects what you think about in day.

111
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:09,320
A' Bi.

112
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:11,558
Thank you.

113
00:07:11,559 --> 00:07:12,519
You're welcome.

114
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:14,158
I don't read many books.

115
00:07:14,159 --> 00:07:17,599
Thanks to Ms. Quan, I have the very basic knowledge.

116
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:19,718
But when I was little, my mom always told me that

117
00:07:19,719 --> 00:07:21,838
one can always lead a good life

118
00:07:21,839 --> 00:07:25,158
if he combs his hair, brushes teeth, cleans his face with tissues

119
00:07:25,159 --> 00:07:28,079
and has three full meals everyday.

120
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:30,039
I think Master is right.

121
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:33,360
You're so clever that you always think too much.

122
00:07:35,159 --> 00:07:38,559
What you just said reflects real wisdom.

123
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:40,639
Yes.

124
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:43,200
Master always says my vague manner conceals a brilliant mind.

125
00:07:43,879 --> 00:07:48,998
By the way, did you call a man A' Sun?

126
00:07:48,999 --> 00:07:50,159
Or it's a monkey you raise?

127
00:07:50,879 --> 00:07:51,959
It's Sun.

128
00:07:52,879 --> 00:07:54,158
Sun?

129
00:07:54,159 --> 00:07:55,719
So it's a bird you raise?

130
00:07:56,559 --> 00:07:58,200
He's my former companion.

131
00:07:59,119 --> 00:08:02,479
Since he's your companion, why doesn't he look for you?

132
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:03,799
I don't think so.

133
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,800
